(42, 1, 20, 26, 3, 26, 26, 'thou shalt be dumb', 'Connection of Speech and Silence', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being made ''dumb'' or unable to speak as a consequence of disbelief or rebellion. This connection highlights the consequences of not heeding divine messages.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 1, 20, 26, 24, 27, 27, 'thou shalt be dumb', 'Connection of Speech and Silence', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''dumb'' and the eventual restoration of speech. Both passages emphasize a divine action that leads to the ability to speak, signifying a fulfillment of God''s promise.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 1, 20, 58, 6, 18, 18, 'believest not my words', 'Connection of Belief and Hope', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief and its consequences. In Luke, disbelief leads to silence, while Hebrews emphasizes the certainty of God''s promises, offering hope to believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
