(42, 1, 26, 43, 7, 41, 41, 'a city of Galilee, named Nazareth', 'Connection of Galilee in Scripture', 'This connection highlights the significance of Galilee as a location in both passages. Luke introduces Nazareth in Galilee as the place of the angel''s announcement, while John raises questions about the Messiah''s origin from Galilee.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 1, 26, 42, 2, 4, 4, 'a city of Galilee, named Nazareth', 'Connection of Nazareth and Galilee', 'Both passages emphasize Galilee and Nazareth as key locations. The first passage introduces Nazareth, while the second confirms Joseph''s origin from this city in Galilee.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 1, 26, 43, 1, 45, 46, 'a city of Galilee, named Nazareth', 'Connection of Nazareth References', 'Both passages emphasize Nazareth as a significant location. Luke introduces Nazareth as the city where Gabriel announces Jesus'' birth, while John identifies Jesus as ''Jesus of Nazareth,'' highlighting its importance in the narrative.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
